{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2392","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2392/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2392/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2392/events","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/2392","id":1170514166,"node_id":"I_kwDOABA2rM5FxKD2","number":2392,"title":"Command line option to skip benchmarks","user":{"login":"nandanvasudevan","id":28172619,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4MTcyNjE5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28172619?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan","html_url":"https://github.com/nandanvasudevan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nandanvasudevan/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":513089975,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw1MTMwODk5NzU=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/labels/Feature%20Request","name":"Feature Request","color":"0e8a16","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2022-03-16T04:07:06Z","updated_at":"2022-04-23T21:14:51Z","closed_at":"2022-04-23T21:14:51Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Description**\r\nEnable or disable benchmarks with a command line option\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nI don't always want to run benchmarks. In the current situation using any `ifdef`s or `#define`s, triggers a complete re-compilation which is really time-consuming and something I really want to avoid.\r\nIt would be really helpful if there was a command line option to disable benchmarks.\r\n\r\n## Possibilities with existing\r\nLets look at what the current options to achieve this are.\r\n### Using Tags\r\nRight now, one plausible way is to keep benchmarks in a separate `TEST_CASE` with a tag that reads 'Benchmark' and then disallow running of that tag which [is supported](https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/blob/38879296a7a0a1787a85d470047fd14d8f6d09aa/docs/command-line.md?plain=1#L110). \r\nHowever, this will almost always lead to code duplication since the setup code will need to be repeated just for the benchmark.\r\n### Using Sections\r\nBy keeping a benchmark as a section in `TEST_CASE` and then running only these sections seems possible.\r\nHowever, there is option to specify, run all except this section.\r\nThis wouldn't work.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/sub